+# Lifecycle attributes inventory
+
+## Purpose
+
+This document records the initial inventory of EDO attributes related to lifecycle-dependent engineering values.
+
+It supports the next lifecycle-attribute refactoring steps without changing the ontology yet.
+
+Rule used in the review:
+
+> If the meaning changes, the concept changes.
+
+This rule must be applied with care. It should not be used to mechanically create every possible combination of lifecycle prefix and attribute name.
+
+## Scope
+
+Source reviewed:
+
+```text
+core/edo.ttl
+```
+
+Families reviewed:
+
+```text
+Length
+WaterDepth / Depth
+Pressure
+Temperature
+BendingRadius
+Tension / Tensile / AxialLoad
+Collapse / Burst
+FatigueLife / DesignLife
+Weight / Mass
+Diameter / Thickness
+```
+
+## General findings
+
+The current EDO already contains many engineering attributes that encode lifecycle or operational meaning in their names, especially in pressure, temperature, tension, diameter, mass and table-column attributes.
+
+The refactoring should not rename these attributes automatically.
+
+The first safe action is to classify selected attributes with:
+
+```ttl
+edo:lifecycleRole
+edo:attributeNature
+```
+
+and only create new attributes when there is a real semantic distinction.
+
+## Length-related attributes found
+
+Existing attributes and columns include:
+
+```text
+NominalLength
+MaxLengthTolerance
+MetallicStrandLength
+WireRopeSlingLength
+StrandsTable_StrandsLength
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+- `NominalLength` appears to be the main generic/domain length attribute.
+- `MaxLengthTolerance` is a tolerance attribute, not a lifecycle value of length itself.
+- `MetallicStrandLength`, `WireRopeSlingLength` and `StrandsTable_StrandsLength` are component/table-specific length attributes.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not create `RequiredLength`, `DesignedLength` or `AsBuiltLength` yet.
+- Revisit length after pressure or water depth, because length is less useful as the first test family for lifecycle-role modelling.
+
+## Water depth / depth attributes found
+
+No explicit `WaterDepth` or `Depth` attribute was found in the reviewed EDO core.
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+This makes water depth a good candidate for a clean first modelling exercise, because it can demonstrate the difference between:
+
+```text
+maximum supported water depth
+installed water depth
+```
+
+Suggested candidate concepts:
+
+```text
+RequiredMaxWaterDepth
+DesignedMaxWaterDepth
+InstalledWaterDepth
+CertifiedMaxWaterDepth
+```
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not create these automatically in this inventory patch.
+- Use water depth as a candidate for the first lifecycle-attribute implementation patch if the goal is a clean example.
+
+## Pressure-related attributes found
+
+Existing attributes and columns include:
+
+```text
+AbsoluteInsidePressure
+AbsoluteOutsidePressure
+CalculatedAbsoluteBurstPressure
+HydrostaticCollapseAbsPressDry
+HydrostaticPressureTestsAttribute
+InternalIncidentalPressureCurveAttribute
+InternalIncidentalPressureTable_Pressure
+LayingMinimumRadiusTable_AbsoluteExternalPressure
+LayingMinimumRadiusTable_AbsoluteInternalPressure
+MaxDesignAbsIntPresTable_Pressure
+MaxDesignPressure
+RingGasketPressureRating
+StressAtDesignPressure
+```
+
+Related classes/components also include pressure in their names, but they are not attributes, for example:
+
+```text
+InternalPressureSheath
+PressureArmour
+PressureComponent
+PressureEquipment
+PressureSensor
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+Pressure is a strong candidate family because the current EDO already contains design, test, incidental, collapse, burst and rating-related pressure concepts.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not merge these under a single generic `Pressure` attribute.
+- Classify existing pressure attributes first with `lifecycleRole` and `attributeNature` where obvious.
+- Create new lifecycle-specific pressure attributes only when the existing concept does not already capture the intended meaning.
+
+Candidate semantic distinctions:
+
+```text
+required pressure
+maximum design pressure
+test pressure
+operating pressure
+burst pressure
+collapse pressure
+certified pressure rating
+```
+
+## Temperature-related attributes found
+
+Existing attributes and columns include:
+
+```text
+MaximumTemperature
+MinimumTemperature
+InsideTemperature
+OutsideTemperature
+MaximumAmbientTemperature
+DiffusionTable_Temperature
+EModVsTempTable_Temperature
+PermeabilityTable_Temperature
+SolubilityTable_Temperature
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+Temperature already appears in both generic attributes and table-column contexts.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not create a full lifecycle temperature family yet.
+- Preserve table-column attributes as table-column concepts.
+- Classify generic temperature attributes only where their lifecycle role is clear.
+
+## Bending radius attributes found
+
+Existing attributes and columns include:
+
+```text
+MinimumBendingRadiusForStorage
+LayingMinimumRadiusTable_MinimumAllowableBendingRadius
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+Bending radius values are context-dependent and should not be collapsed into a single generic radius attribute.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Treat storage and laying/installability contexts separately.
+- Do not refactor in the first lifecycle family unless needed.
+
+## Tension / tensile / axial-load attributes found
+
+Existing attributes and columns include:
+
+```text
+AxialStiffnessUnderCompressionAtSeaLevel
+AxialStiffnessUnderTensionAtSeaLevel
+MaximumAllowableTensileForStraightLine
+MaximumAllowableTensionTable_MaximumAllowableTensile
+MaximumAllowableTighteningTable_AxialLoad
+SpoolingTension
+TensileArmourAnnulusCondition
+TensileArmourFreeAnnulusVolume
+TensileWireLayAngle
+TensileWiresCount
+UltimateTensileStress
+```
+
+Related classes/components include:
+
+```text
+TensileArmour
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+This family mixes force, stress, stiffness, installation/load cases and component structure.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not use this as the first lifecycle family.
+- Revisit after pressure and water depth.
+
+## Collapse / burst attributes found
+
+Existing attributes include:
+
+```text
+CalculatedAbsoluteBurstPressure
+HydrostaticCollapseAbsPressDry
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+These are capability/resistance concepts and should likely receive `CapabilityAttribute` plus a mechanical nature.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Treat as pressure-related capability attributes.
+- Do not rename automatically.
+
+## Fatigue life / design life attributes found
+
+No explicit matching attributes were found in the initial scan.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Leave for future review.
+
+## Weight / mass attributes found
+
+Existing attributes include:
+
+```text
+Mass
+LinearMass
+IndividualAnodeMass
+SpecificWeight
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+Mass and weight should not be treated as synonyms.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not refactor in the first lifecycle family.
+- Preserve distinction between mass, linear mass and specific weight.
+
+## Diameter / thickness attributes found
+
+Existing attributes include:
+
+```text
+BoreDiameter
+ClampInternalDiameter
+CollarInternalDiameter
+ExternalDiameter
+GrooveDiameter
+GrooveSupportSurfaceDiameter
+InternalDiameter
+LayerGeometryProfileThickness
+LayerGeometryThickness
+LayerThickness
+NominalDiameter
+OuterDiameter
+RingGasketInnerDIameter
+RingGasketOuterDiameter
+ShackleInnerDiameter
+ShackleOuterDiameter
+ShackleThickness
+UpperItubeDiameter
+WireRopeSlingDiameter
+```
+
+Initial assessment:
+
+Diameter and thickness attributes are mostly component-specific or geometry-specific.
+
+Suggested action:
+
+- Do not create lifecycle variants mechanically.
+- Classify with `DimensionalAttribute` when useful.
+
+## Recommended first implementation family
+
+Two good candidates remain:
+
+```text
+WaterDepth
+Pressure
+```
+
+Recommended approach:
+
+1. Use `WaterDepth` if the goal is a clean modelling example with few legacy conflicts.
+2. Use `Pressure` if the goal is to classify and improve an already rich area of the ontology.
+
+## Proposed next patch
+
+The next lifecycle patch should choose one family only.
+
+Recommended next patch:
+
+```text
+Patch 14 — First lifecycle attribute family
+Candidate: WaterDepth or Pressure
+```
+
+Before generating Patch 14, decide which family will be implemented first.
+
+## Items explicitly not changed by this inventory
+
+This inventory does not:
+
+```text
+rename existing attributes
+remove existing attributes
+create lifecycle-specific attributes
+add lifecycleRole to existing attributes
+add attributeNature to existing attributes
+change data contracts
+change EDO-IFC mappings
+```
